org.transitime.db.structs

Class Trip

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.transitime.db.structs.Trip
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, org.hibernate.classic.Lifecycle

    @Entity
public class Trip
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.hibernate.classic.Lifecycle, java.io.Serializable
    Describes a GTFS trip but also includes travel time information.

    Serializable since Hibernate requires such.

    Implements Lifecycle so that can have the onLoad() callback be called when reading in data so that can intern() member strings. In order to do this the String members could not be declared as final since they are updated after the constructor is called.

    Author:
    SkiBu Smith
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • Trip

        public Trip(int configRev,
            GtfsTrip gtfsTrip,
            java.lang.String properRouteId,
            java.lang.String routeShortName,
            TitleFormatter titleFormatter)
        Constructs Trip object from GTFS data.

        Does not set startTime nor endTime. Those are set separately using addScheduleTimes(). Also doesn't set travel times. Those are set separately using setTravelTimes().

        Parameters:
        configRev -
        gtfsTrip - The GTFS data describing the trip
        properRouteId - The routeId, but can actually be the ID of the parent route.
        routeShortName - Needed to provide a route identifier that is consistent over schedule changes.
        titleFormatter - So can fix titles associated with trip

      • Trip

        public Trip(Trip tripFromStopTimes,
            int frequenciesBasedStartTime)
        Creates a copy of the Trip object but adjusts the startTime, endTime, and scheduledTimesMap according to the frequenciesBasedStartTime. This is used when the frequencies.txt file specifies exact_times for a trip.
        Parameters:
        tripFromStopTimes -
        frequenciesBasedStartTime -

      • Trip

        public Trip(Trip tripFromStopTimes,
            int frequenciesBasedStartTime,
            int frequenciesBasedEndTime)
        Creates a copy of the Trip object but adjusts the startTime, endTime, and scheduledTimesMap according to the frequenciesBasedStartTime. This is used when the frequencies.txt specifies a time range for a trip but where exact_times is false. This is for noSchedule routes where vehicle is expected to continuously run on a route without a schedule.
        Parameters:
        tripFromStopTimes -
        frequenciesBasedStartTime -
        frequenciesBasedEndTime -

      • getStartTime

        public java.lang.Integer getStartTime()
        Returns departure time of first stop of trip. Gtfs requires departure time of first stop of trip and arrival time of last stop of trip to be set, even for unscheduled blocks. That way they can determine running time of trip.
        Returns:
        departure time of first stop of trip. Time is seconds into the day. Can be null.

      • getEndTime

        public java.lang.Integer getEndTime()
        Returns arrival time of last stop of trip. Gtfs requires departure time of first stop of trip and arrival time of last stop of trip to be set, even for unscheduled blocks. That way they can determine running time of trip.
        Returns:
        arrival time of last stop of trip. Time is seconds into the day. Can be null.
